xu: 1
kind: ApplicationBuildRunbook
metadata:
  name: i-want-to-check-if-this-was-done-the-user-is-una
  owner: local
  status: draft
  mode: review
intent:
  rawPrompt: >-
    i want to check if this was done 


    The user is unavailable. I'll commit to the recommended options and produce the plan
    autonomously. Decisions:


    Blackbox PDF: I'll use the public Blackbox.ai homepage as the visual/structural reference during
    the marketing rebuild.

    Screenshot input: Xupra Pro AI only (vision tokens billed to you only for Pro users).

    Clarifying questions: One round, 2–4 questions, then plan.

    Enterprise mode: Auto-detect — if Pro API unreachable, silently fall back to External AI Prompt
    with a banner.

    Shipping: Slice-by-slice — each ticket = commit + version bump + push.

    Plan: Zero-Friction Build Sessions + Marketing Rebuild

    End-to-end build that delivers your vision: paste prompt/screenshot → AI asks 2–4 clarifying
    questions → planner generates a runbook → kanban with visible per-step status → drag to reorder
    → pick agent → click Handoff → tick steps off → next phase auto-activates. Plus Blackbox-style
    marketing rebuild and enterprise/air-gapped fallback. Ships in slices: each ticket = commit +
    extension version bump + push.


    Phases


    A — Provider transparency (T1)

    B — Step model migration (T2)

    C — Kanban execution UX (T3, T4, T5)

    D — Clarifying-question loop (T6)

    E — Multimodal paste (T7)

    F — Enterprise / air-gapped fallback (T8)

    G — Marketing rebuild (T9, parallel)

    Tickets


    T1 — Planning AI status banner (Control Room + sidebar). Provider resolver returns {provider,
    reason}. → 0.2.6

    T2 — XuStep type with per-step status; normalizeSteps() keeps legacy string[] runbooks working.
    → 0.2.7

    T3 — Render steps as a checklist inside each phase card; checkbox toggles pending → active →
    complete. → 0.2.8

    T4 — Per-phase Handoff button with agent-specific routing (Claude Code opens file, Cursor copies
    for Composer, Copilot opens chat, Codex copies, External opens side-by-side). → 0.2.9

    T5 — Auto-advance: phase complete → next phase active; "Continue" always points to active phase.
    → 0.3.0

    T6 — Clarifying-question chat loop. New POST /api/v1/drylake/runbooks/clarify. Provider gets
    clarify() method. → 0.3.1

    T7 — Screenshot paste in prompt textarea. Pro-only vision; LM/clipboard ignore images with
    notice. → 0.3.2

    T8 — Enterprise mode: drylake.forceExternalAiPrompt setting + health-probe fallback. → 0.3.3

    T9 — Marketing homepage rebuild in Blackbox.ai's visual idiom (dark hero, agent logos,
    three-step explainer, pricing). Parallel.

    Relevant files — full list saved in memories/session/plan.md. Key paths:


    providerResolver.ts, DryLakeAiProvider.ts, provider implementations

    types.ts, parseXu.ts, renderXu.ts

    controlRoomProvider.ts, commands/runbooks.ts

    New: app/api/v1/drylake/runbooks/clarify/route.ts

    page.tsx, app-home.tsx

    Verification (per slice)


    npm run typecheck && npm test && npm run build in extension

    npm run package:vsix && npm run install:vsix; confirm new version; clean VSIX

    Commit + push to origin/development (auto-deploys server to staging)

    End-to-end manual check (after T1–T8)


    Paste prompt → see active planning AI in banner

    Answer clarifying questions → kanban appears

    Each card shows a step checklist

    Drag phase → persists

    Click Handoff → correct coding agent launches

    Tick steps → phase auto-advances

    Toggle forceExternalAiPrompt → banner switches to clipboard mode

    Pro user pastes screenshot → thumbnail + runbook references image

    Decisions locked autonomously


    Slice shipping, each ticket = own commit + version bump on development

    VS Code LM stays in auto chain (free Copilot users keep AI planning)

    Vision tokens billed only for Pro

    Production deploy held until you explicitly approve

    Blackbox.ai is structural inspiration only — no copy/asset reuse

    Further considerations


    Step ID format ${phase.id}.${index+1} (e.g. 1.1) for legacy migration — flag if you want
    different (P1-S1 etc.).

    T8 health probe adds ~3s startup latency; I'll cache the result 60s per session to keep startup
    snappy.

    Marketing demo GIF/video — record in final pass after T1–T5 are live so the demo matches the new
    UX. Static screenshots until then.

    Plan saved to memories/session/plan.md. Use the handoff buttons to execute, or reply with
    changes you want.
  purpose: i want to check if this was done The user is unavailable.
  users:
    - developer
  goals:
    - Create an inspectable drylake.xu runbook.
    - Confirm purpose before architecture work.
    - Approve architecture before execution handoff.
    - Generate native agent files from the approved runbook.
  nonGoals:
    - Do not deploy or publish from this runbook.
    - Do not run provisioning commands automatically.
    - Do not call production APIs from the runbook flow.
  constraints:
    - Local-first workflow.
    - Preview provisioning before execution.
    - Keep generated artifacts under .drylake/generated first.
    - Preserve user files with backups before overwrite.
confirmation:
  required: true
  status: pending
  userApprovedIntent: false
  userApprovedArchitecture: false
  userApprovedProvisioning: false
architecture:
  status: proposed
  summary: >-
    Use the current workspace as the source of truth (Workspace: agenttransfer). Keep the runbook,
    approvals, generated files, and phase handoffs inspectable on disk.
  decisions:
    - id: ADR-001
      choice: Use drylake.xu as the workflow source of truth.
      rationale: >-
        The user can inspect and version purpose, constraints, architecture, phases, and handoff
        instructions.
    - id: ADR-002
      choice: Generate preview artifacts before installing root instruction files.
      rationale: Preview-first generation makes the workflow safe to test in development.
  risks:
    - The generated draft is local and deterministic when no integrated AI is available.
    - Execution still depends on the user's chosen coding agent.
  assumptions:
    - The user will approve purpose and architecture before execution.
    - Provisioning commands are reviewed manually.
provisioning:
  status: draft
  commands:
    - npm install
    - npm run build
  filesToCreate:
    - .drylake/generated/RUNBOOK.md
    - .drylake/generated/AGENTS.md
    - .drylake/generated/CLAUDE.md
  environmentVariables: []
  externalServices: []
  safety:
    requiresApprovalBeforeExecution: true
    executeAutomatically: false
phases:
  - id: 01-intake
    title: Confirm application purpose
    agent: copilot
    gate: user-confirmation
    status: pending
    objective: Confirm what the user wants built.
    inputs:
      - user prompt
    outputs:
      - confirmed purpose
      - goals
      - non-goals
      - constraints
    steps:
      - id: 01-intake-step-01
        text: Parse the user prompt.
        status: pending
      - id: 01-intake-step-02
        text: Identify the application purpose.
        status: pending
      - id: 01-intake-step-03
        text: Identify target users.
        status: pending
      - id: 01-intake-step-04
        text: Identify non-goals and constraints.
        status: pending
      - id: 01-intake-step-05
        text: Ask the user to confirm before architecture work starts.
        status: pending
    acceptance:
      - Purpose is confirmed.
      - Goals and non-goals are explicit.
      - Constraints are recorded.
  - id: 02-architecture
    title: Approve architecture
    agent: copilot
    gate: architecture-approval
    status: pending
    objective: Agree on technical architecture before implementation.
    inputs: []
    outputs: []
    steps:
      - id: 02-architecture-step-01
        text: Propose architecture.
        status: pending
      - id: 02-architecture-step-02
        text: List major dependencies.
        status: pending
      - id: 02-architecture-step-03
        text: List data model assumptions.
        status: pending
      - id: 02-architecture-step-04
        text: List deployment assumptions.
        status: pending
      - id: 02-architecture-step-05
        text: Ask the user to approve or revise.
        status: pending
    acceptance:
      - Architecture is approved.
      - Risks and assumptions are documented.
  - id: 03-provisioning
    title: Preview provisioning
    agent: copilot
    gate: provisioning-approval
    status: pending
    objective: Preview project setup, commands, files, and environment requirements.
    inputs: []
    outputs: []
    steps:
      - id: 03-provisioning-step-01
        text: Generate setup commands.
        status: pending
      - id: 03-provisioning-step-02
        text: Generate file creation plan.
        status: pending
      - id: 03-provisioning-step-03
        text: Generate environment variable list.
        status: pending
      - id: 03-provisioning-step-04
        text: Require approval before running or handing off commands.
        status: pending
    acceptance:
      - Provisioning plan is approved.
      - No command executes without user confirmation.
  - id: 04-implementation
    title: Implement in vertical slices
    agent: copilot
    gate: phase-review
    status: pending
    objective: Build the application step by step.
    inputs: []
    outputs: []
    steps:
      - id: 04-implementation-step-01
        text: Implement one thin vertical slice.
        status: pending
      - id: 04-implementation-step-02
        text: Avoid unrelated refactors.
        status: pending
      - id: 04-implementation-step-03
        text: Keep changes reversible.
        status: pending
      - id: 04-implementation-step-04
        text: Verify each phase before continuing.
        status: pending
    acceptance:
      - Changed files are summarized.
      - Checks pass or failures are explained.
  - id: 05-verification
    title: Verify and hand off
    agent: copilot
    gate: final-review
    status: pending
    objective: Validate implementation and produce final handoff.
    inputs: []
    outputs: []
    steps:
      - id: 05-verification-step-01
        text: Run build.
        status: pending
      - id: 05-verification-step-02
        text: Run tests.
        status: pending
      - id: 05-verification-step-03
        text: Run lint.
        status: pending
      - id: 05-verification-step-04
        text: Summarize changed files.
        status: pending
      - id: 05-verification-step-05
        text: Summarize remaining risks.
        status: pending
    acceptance:
      - Verification is complete.
      - Handoff notes are generated.
checks:
  install: npm install
  dev: npm run dev
  build: npm run build
  test: npm test
  lint: npm run lint
agentTargets:
  agentsMd: true
  claudeMd: true
  copilotInstructions: true
  cursorRules: true
  codexSkill: true
  openclawSkill: true
handoff:
  defaultAgent: claude-code
  instructions:
    - Follow phases in order.
    - Do not skip approval gates.
    - Do not provision infrastructure without explicit confirmation.
    - Always summarize changed files and verification results.
